-- 7. Dover × Digital Marketing
INSERT INTO public.local_content (service_slug, town_slug, intro_paragraph, local_context, competition_landscape, success_approach, local_stats, pain_points, solutions, faqs, layout_variant)
VALUES (
  'digital-marketing',
  'dover',
  'Dover offers a marketing landscape that most digital agencies completely misunderstand. This is not simply a small Kent town with a local audience. It is the busiest passenger port in the United Kingdom, home to one of England''s most visited castles, and the location of the White Cliffs, one of Britain''s most recognisable landmarks. The marketing opportunity here is dual-natured: a resident population of thirty-five thousand who need everyday services, and millions of annual visitors who spend money on food, accommodation, retail, and experiences. Yet most Dover businesses market only to one of these audiences, or worse, to neither with any deliberate strategy. Our digital marketing campaigns are built specifically for Dover''s unique dual market, running targeted campaigns that capture local customers while intercepting the enormous visitor traffic that passes through this town every year.',
  'Dover''s digital marketing environment spans three distinct audiences. Local residents search for services, shop online, and respond to social media advertising in standard patterns. Tourists plan visits through Google, social media, and travel platforms, with decision-making often happening weeks before arrival. The port logistics and commercial sector operates through B2B channels including LinkedIn, industry directories, and trade publications. Dover Priory station, the A2/A20 corridors, and the ferry terminal create additional geographic targeting opportunities for reaching travellers at specific points in their journey.',
  'Digital marketing spend in Dover is concentrated among a small number of tourism operators and hospitality businesses running Google Ads and social campaigns. The broader business community invests minimally in paid digital channels. National tourism boards and ferry operators dominate the paid search landscape for crossing and visit-related terms. Local service businesses face moderate competition from regional competitors but very little from sophisticated local campaigns.',
  'We build Dover digital marketing campaigns around audience segmentation and timing. Tourist-targeted ads launch before peak booking periods with messaging tied to Castle visits, Cliffs walks, and port crossings. Local service campaigns run year-round targeting residents across the district. Remarketing captures website visitors who browsed but did not convert. Every campaign is measured against real business outcomes: enquiries, bookings, and revenue, not vanity metrics.',
  '{"population": 35000, "district_population": 117000, "business_districts": ["Market Square", "High Street", "Port of Dover", "De Bradelei Wharf"], "key_fact": "Dual market opportunity combining resident customers and millions of annual visitors"}',
  '[{"title": "Tourist marketing budget wasted on wrong timing and targeting", "description": "Dover hospitality businesses that run Google Ads or social campaigns often target broadly and year-round, burning budget during low-season periods and missing the critical pre-booking window when tourists decide where to eat, stay, and visit. Without seasonal campaign management, marketing spend generates far fewer bookings than it should."}, {"title": "Local service businesses invisible in Dover''s digital landscape", "description": "While tourism operators invest in some digital marketing, most Dover trades, professional services, and retailers do zero paid digital advertising. They rely entirely on word of mouth and organic search in a market where competitors in neighbouring towns are actively advertising to Dover residents."}, {"title": "No remarketing strategy for Dover website visitors who leave", "description": "A tourist visits your Dover restaurant website while planning a White Cliffs trip but does not book immediately. A resident checks your plumbing prices but gets distracted. Without remarketing campaigns that follow these visitors across the web and social media, you lose them permanently to the next search result."}]',
  '[{"title": "Seasonal tourism campaigns timed to Dover''s visitor calendar", "description": "We launch tourist-targeted campaigns before peak booking windows, not during them. Google Ads and social campaigns promoting your Dover business reach visitors while they are planning their White Cliffs walk, Castle visit, or port crossing. By the time they arrive, they have already chosen your business."}, {"title": "Year-round local campaigns for Dover''s resident market", "description": "Targeted Google Ads and social media campaigns reach Dover district residents searching for everyday services. Postcode-level targeting ensures your budget reaches the right audience across the town and surrounding areas. Campaign messaging reflects local knowledge, building trust that generic national advertisers cannot match."}, {"title": "Remarketing campaigns converting Dover browsers into customers", "description": "Visitors who browse your Dover website without converting see targeted follow-up ads across Google, Facebook, and Instagram. A tourist who checked your restaurant menu sees a booking prompt on their Facebook feed that evening. A resident who browsed your services sees a reminder ad the following day."}]',
  '[{"question": "How much should a Dover business spend on digital marketing?", "answer": "It depends on your audience and goals. A Dover restaurant targeting tourist traffic might invest heavily during spring and summer. A local trade business needs a steady year-round budget. We typically recommend starting with a focused budget of a few hundred pounds monthly, scaling based on measurable return on investment."}, {"question": "Can you run campaigns targeting tourists before they arrive in Dover?", "answer": "Absolutely. We target people searching for Dover Castle, White Cliffs walks, ferry crossings, and Dover accommodation in the weeks before peak tourist periods. By the time they arrive, they have already seen your business and formed a positive impression. This pre-arrival advertising is highly effective."}, {"question": "Which platforms work best for Dover digital marketing?", "answer": "Google Ads captures high-intent searches from both residents and tourists. Facebook and Instagram reach tourists during trip planning and residents during leisure browsing. For B2B and logistics, LinkedIn campaigns target commercial decision-makers. We recommend the platform mix that matches your specific audience."}, {"question": "How do I know if my Dover marketing campaigns are working?", "answer": "We provide monthly reporting showing exactly how many enquiries, bookings, or sales each campaign generated. No vanity metrics. You see which Dover campaigns drove real business outcomes, what each lead cost, and where to increase or reduce spend for maximum return on investment."}]',
  'lead-gen'
)
